snippet.textDisplay:
A huge shoutout to Aahad Nyani (drummer), Kamran Zafar (bass player), Sheroze Hussain(sitaar player) because they were brilliant! Say what you want about the song but no one is doubting their genius capabilities. 

Now, Samra is amazing and her voice has poise and beauty to it. I think her voice was haunting. Face it, we can't keep thinking of this track as the cover of a Madam Noor Jehan song. It's a whole new song now and it's awesome. I really hope Asim comes back because, I'm really curious about what he can sing and his range appears to be crazy! They both hit their notes so smoothly. The facts that Asim was singing in Punjabi and the contrast there was between the two gave the song a lot of depth.  

I haven't been too crazy about  songs that have two different styles in one but, that appears to be how the producers want to create and showcase. It's starting to grow on me. Loved this track overall.

A lot of people are saying Asim Azhar ruined the song..but let's be honest here, as a singer he's improved A LOT. His voice has matured and has finally started to find his own style. He's only 18 and i think all of you guys  are expecting him to sound like someone with 20 years of experience.... in a song that isn't his kind of genre.

 I think they both sounded fine and i can understand if both singers were "mismatched" but in my opinion they were seriously not that bad. As for the singers, the instrumentals were on point and drummer seemed to be having a good time.
